{"id": 28, "ts": 1778775081.7309895, "event": "public_discussion_message", "round": 1, "agent": "agent_2", "message": "From the data we have, each candidate shows a mix of strengths and weaknesses:\n**Candidate\u202fA** \u2013 strong technical perception (anticipates danger, excellent spatial vision, sees complex connections) and good leadership, but is seen as a show\u2011off and not open to new ideas, with no evidence of stress resilience or calmness under pressure.\n**Candidate\u202fB** \u2013 very conscientious, handles stress well, assesses weather accurately and has excellent computer skills \u2013 all vital for long\u2011haul operations. However, a weak memory for numbers and a habit of making nasty remarks toward colleagues raise concerns about reliability in calculations and crew cohesion. No documented teamwork or communication strengths.\n**Candidate\u202fC** \u2013 makes quick, correct decisions, stays calm in a crisis, understands complicated technology and creates a positive atmosphere with the crew. The main drawbacks are difficulty communicating ideas, an egocentric attitude and a lack of willingness to pursue further education, which could affect long\u2011term development and precise cockpit communication.\n**Candidate\u202fD** \u2013 solves problems exceptionally, takes responsibility seriously, concentrates well and responds adequately to unexpected events, indicating solid judgment under pressure. Yet a hot temper, being regarded as a know\u2011it\u2011all and the absence of any noted teamwork or communication strengths suggest potential crew\u2011interaction problems.\nFor long\u2011distance flights the most critical factors are reliable decision\u2011making, stress resilience, technical competence (especially weather and systems knowledge), and the ability to work smoothly with the crew. Candidate\u202fC uniquely combines quick, correct decision\u2011making, calmness in crises, strong technical understanding and a demonstrable positive crew atmosphere, outweighing the communication\u2011style concerns. The other candidates each have a more serious deficit in either reliability, crew interaction, or professional development.\n**Therefore I support Candidate\u202fC.**\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
