al competence (especially weather and systems knowledge), and effective crew interaction**. Candidate\u202fC uniquely combines proven reliability, rapid correct decision\u2011making, calmness in crises, solid technical understanding, and a demonstrably positive crew atmosphere. While his communication style and professional\u2011development attitude are concerns, they are outweighed by the breadth of his strengths and the more severe safety\u2011related weaknesses seen in the other candidates (memory for numbers in B, hot temper in D, and lack of core reliability/pressure handling in A).\n**Therefore I support Candidate\u202fC.**\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate C\"}"}
